<p>New York City residents benefit from multiple layers of solar incentives that dramatically reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on the total system cost through 2032, with no cap on residential systems. New York State offers additional incentives through the NY-Sun program, providing upfront rebates of \$0.20-\$0.40 per watt depending on system size and installer participation. The state also offers a 25% tax credit up to \$5,000 for solar installations. ConEd customers can participate in net metering, earning credits for excess electricity fed back to the grid at the full retail rate of 21.5¬¢/kWh. Additionally, solar installations are exempt from state and local sales taxes, and the added home value from solar panels is exempt from property tax increases for 15 years under the Solar Energy System Exemption.</p>

